hpnicfDot11CFG.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Association The service used to establish access point or station mapping and enable station invocation of the distribution system services. (Wireless clients attempt to connect to access points.) Basic Rate A data rate that is mandatory for client devices to support in order for them to achieve successful association. MSDU MAC Service Data Unit, it is frame format defined by 802.11. TU It is 1,024 microseconds (ms), which is about 1 millisecond. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

hpnicfDot11GlobalCountryCode.name: hpnicfDot11GlobalCountryCode
hpnicfDot11GlobalCountryCode.description: Represents the country code for wireless network.

hpnicfDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.name: hpnicfDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl
hpnicfDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA. Default value 0 : The keep alive function is disabled.

hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.name: hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl
hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

hpnicfDot11BroadcastProbeReply.name: hpnicfDot11BroadcastProbeReply
hpnicfDot11BroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

hpnicfDot11APScanMode.name: hpnicfDot11APScanMode
hpnicfDot11APScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode for AP. The following values are supported: active - AP will actively do scan. passive - AP will passively do scan.

hpnicfDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.name: hpnicfDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport
hpnicfDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP Control tunnel.

hpnicfDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.name: hpnicfDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport
hpnicfDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP data tunnel. The cleartxt is the default scheme.

hpnicfDot11ACAutoAPSupport.name: hpnicfDot11ACAutoAPSupport
hpnicfDot11ACAutoAPSupport.description: Represents enable the auto AP functionality or not. 'true' : The auto AP functionality is enabled. 'false': The auto AP functionality is disabled

hpnicfDot11AutoAPName.name: hpnicfDot11AutoAPName
hpnicfDot11AutoAPName.description: Represents the name of auto AP that needs to be made persistent. When read the value from the node, NULL value be returned.

hpnicfDot11PersistentName.name: hpnicfDot11PersistentName
hpnicfDot11PersistentName.description: Represents the new name of auto AP after being made persistent. When read the value from the node, NULL value be returned.

hpnicfDot11IntfTrapThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11IntfTrapThreshold
hpnicfDot11IntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

hpnicfDot11MonitorInterval.name: hpnicfDot11MonitorInterval
hpnicfDot11MonitorInterval.description: Represents the monitoring interval. Default value 0 : The monitoring functionality is changed to real-time mode.

hpnicfDot11SampleInterval.name: hpnicfDot11SampleInterval
hpnicfDot11SampleInterval.description: Represents the sampling interval. Default value 0 : The sampling functionality is disabled.

hpnicfDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.name: hpnicfDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval
hpnicfDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.description: Represents the checking interval of channel switch.

hpnicfDot11APUserUplimit.name: hpnicfDot11APUserUplimit
hpnicfDot11APUserUplimit.description: Represents the upper limit of user which has access to this AP.

hpnicfDot11APL2IsolateEnable.name: hpnicfDot11APL2IsolateEnable
hpnicfDot11APL2IsolateEnable.description: Represents enable the layer2 isolation or not. 'true' : The layer2 isolation functionality is enabled. 'false': The layer2 isolation functionality is disabled.

hpnicfDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.name: hpnicfDot11APBSSIDSupportNum
hpnicfDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.description: Represents the max number of BSSID supported by Current AP.

hpnicfDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.name: hpnicfDot11APLastUpdateStatTime
hpnicfDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.description: Represents date and time update statistic information lately.

hpnicfDot11APDoSProtectEnable.name: hpnicfDot11APDoSProtectEnable
hpnicfDot11APDoSProtectEnable.description: Represents enable the DOS protection or not. 'true' : The DOS protection functionality is enabled. 'false': The DOS protection functionality is disabled.

hpnicfDot11MaxAPPerIf.name: hpnicfDot11MaxAPPerIf
hpnicfDot11MaxAPPerIf.description: Represents max AP number that can be connected to AC interface.

hpnicfDot11SampleTimeStamp.name: hpnicfDot11SampleTimeStamp
hpnicfDot11SampleTimeStamp.description: Represents the start time of current sample period.

hpnicfDot11UplinkTrackId.name: hpnicfDot11UplinkTrackId
hpnicfDot11UplinkTrackId.description: Represents the track id of AP. Default value 0 : The uplink track function for AP is disabled.

hpnicfDot11RtCollectSwitch.name: hpnicfDot11RtCollectSwitch
hpnicfDot11RtCollectSwitch.description: This object is used to turn on/off real-time statistics collection between AC and AP. If the value is true, hpnicfDot11RtCollectIntvl will take effect. Otherwise, hpnicfDot11RglCollectIntvl will take effect.

hpnicfDot11RglCollectIntvl.name: hpnicfDot11RglCollectIntvl
hpnicfDot11RglCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to regularly collect statistics from AC to AP.

hpnicfDot11RtCollectIntvl.name: hpnicfDot11RtCollectIntvl
hpnicfDot11RtCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to collect real-time statistics from AC to AP.

hpnicfDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold
hpnicfDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.description: The CPU usage threshold for all AP.

hpnicfDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold
hpnicfDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.description: The memory usage threshold for all AP.

hpnicfDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold
hpnicfDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of adjacent interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

hpnicfDot11AllAPMonitorMode.name: hpnicfDot11AllAPMonitorMode
hpnicfDot11AllAPMonitorMode.description: Represents what work mode for All AP. The following values are supported: normal, - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

hpnicfDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState.name: hpnicfDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState
hpnicfDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState.description: Represents the status of version auto-update for an AP. The following values are supported: enable - AP version will be updated automatically. disable - AP version will not be updated automatically.

hpnicfDot11ACNasIDCM.name: hpnicfDot11ACNasIDCM
hpnicfDot11ACNasIDCM.description: Represents the NAS-ID of current AC.

hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyTable.name: hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyTable
hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for radio policy, as per radio policy of CLI. One radio policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyEntry.name: hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyEntry
hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyName.name: hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyName
hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyName.description: Represents the name of radio policy.

hpnicfDot11BeaconInterval.name: hpnicfDot11BeaconInterval
hpnicfDot11BeaconInterval.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hpnicfDot11DtimInterval.name: hpnicfDot11DtimInterval
hpnicfDot11DtimInterval.description: Represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

hpnicfDot11RtsThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11RtsThreshold
hpnicfDot11RtsThreshold.description: Represents the current minimum size, in octets, of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

hpnicfDot11FragThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11FragThreshold
hpnicfDot11FragThreshold.description: Represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

hpnicfDot11ShortRetryThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11ShortRetryThreshold
hpnicfDot11ShortRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to hpnicfDot11RTSThreshold, which shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hpnicfDot11LongRetryThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11LongRetryThreshold
hpnicfDot11LongRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than hpnicfDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hpnicfDot11MaxRxLifetime.name: hpnicfDot11MaxRxLifetime
hpnicfDot11MaxRxLifetime.description: Represents the elapsed time. After the time specified by hpnicfDot11MaxRxLifetime, the further attempts to reassemble the MSDU shall be terminated.

hpnicfDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus
hpnicfDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11RdoClientMaxCount.name: hpnicfDot11RdoClientMaxCount
hpnicfDot11RdoClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

hpnicfDot11BeaconIntervalMs.name: hpnicfDot11BeaconIntervalMs
hpnicfDot11BeaconIntervalMs.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyTable.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyTable
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. One service policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyEntry.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyEntry
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyID.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyID
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11SSIDName.name: hpnicfDot11SSIDName
hpnicfDot11SSIDName.description: Represents the ESS. As per CLI, the value of service policy name will be SSID.

hpnicfDot11SSIDHidden.name: hpnicfDot11SSIDHidden
hpnicfDot11SSIDHidden.description: This attribute controls whether the SSID will be advertised in the beacon frame. If it is true, then SSID will not be advertised in the beacon frame.

hpnicfDot11AuthenMode.name: hpnicfDot11AuthenMode
hpnicfDot11AuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hpnicfDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.name: hpnicfDot11SSIDEncryptionMode
hpnicfDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingType.name: hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingType
hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingType.description: Represents the service policy will bind to what kind of data forwarding interface.

hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingID.name: hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingID
hpnicfDot11WlanInfBindingID.description: Represents the interface ID of the interface that ESS will bind to. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed.

hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus
hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11ClientMaxCount.name: hpnicfDot11ClientMaxCount
hpnicfDot11ClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this service policy.

hpnicfDot11SPInCirMode.name: hpnicfDot11SPInCirMode
hpnicfDot11SPInCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of inbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

hpnicfDot11SPInCirValue.name: hpnicfDot11SPInCirValue
hpnicfDot11SPInCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

hpnicfDot11SPOutCirMode.name: hpnicfDot11SPOutCirMode
hpnicfDot11SPOutCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of outbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

hpnicfDot11SPOutCirValue.name: hpnicfDot11SPOutCirValue
hpnicfDot11SPOutCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

hpnicfDot11WlanInfPVID.name: hpnicfDot11WlanInfPVID
hpnicfDot11WlanInfPVID.description: Represents the VLAN ID of SSID.

hpnicfDot11SPInCirStaticValue.name: hpnicfDot11SPInCirStaticValue
hpnicfDot11SPInCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction for static CIR mode.

hpnicfDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.name: hpnicfDot11SPOutCirStaticValue
hpnicfDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction for static CIR mode.

hpnicfDot11SPIsolate.name: hpnicfDot11SPIsolate
hpnicfDot11SPIsolate.description: If it is true, then stations connected with the service policy are isolated.

hpnicfDot11WlanexAuthServerIP.name: hpnicfDot11WlanexAuthServerIP
hpnicfDot11WlanexAuthServerIP.description: Represents the IP address of the Wlanex Authentication server

hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable
hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable.description: If it is true, then beacon-measurement is enabled.

hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasType.name: hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasType
hpnicfDot11SPBeaconMeasType.description: Represents what the work mode for BeaconMeasurement type. The following values are supported: passive, - BeaconMeasurement will use the passive type. active - BeaconMeasurement will use the active type. beaconTable - BeaconMeasurement will use the beacon table type.

hpnicfDot11AuthenModeCM.name: hpnicfDot11AuthenModeCM
hpnicfDot11AuthenModeCM.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hpnicfDot11SecIEStatusCM.name: hpnicfDot11SecIEStatusCM
hpnicfDot11SecIEStatusCM.description: To enable the security Information element in the beacon and probe response frames sent by AP.

hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphersCM.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphersCM
hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphersCM.description: The WLAN system support the following cipher type for data frame encryption. none wep40 wep104 tkip aesccmp wpi-SMS4 When the value of node equals to zero, it means no configuration or undo operation.

hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM
hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM.description: The status of the Service Policy.

hpnicfDot11SSIDHiddenCM.name: hpnicfDot11SSIDHiddenCM
hpnicfDot11SSIDHiddenCM.description: This attribute controls whether the SSID will be advertised in beacon frames. If it is dot11true, the SSID will not be advertised in beacon frames.

hpnicfDot11SPIsolateCM.name: hpnicfDot11SPIsolateCM
hpnicfDot11SPIsolateCM.description: If it is dot11true, the clients connected with the service policy are isolated to each other.

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtTable
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. When the value of hpnicfDot11SSIDEncryptionMode equals to cipher(2), more configuration for a ESS will be put into the table.

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy under cipher(2) mode.

hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtID.name: hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtID
hpnicfDot11ServicePolicyExtID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11SecIEStatus.name: hpnicfDot11SecIEStatus
hpnicfDot11SecIEStatus.description: To enable the security Information element in the beacon and probe response frames sent by AP.

hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphers.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphers
hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphers.description: The WLAN system support the following cipher type for data frame encryption. wep40(2) tkip(4) aesccmp(16) wep104(32) wpisms4(64) wep128(128) For each service policy, it could support multiple cipher types at the same time. So the value of object could combine multiple value of cipher type above. When the value of node equals to zero, it means no configuration or undo operation.

hpnicfDot11CipherKeyIndex.name: hpnicfDot11CipherKeyIndex
hpnicfDot11CipherKeyIndex.description: Represents the key index of cipher key for packet. When hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

hpnicfDot11CipherKey.name: hpnicfDot11CipherKey
hpnicfDot11CipherKey.description: Represents the cipher key for packet. When hpnicfDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus
hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11CipherKeyType.name: hpnicfDot11CipherKeyType
hpnicfDot11CipherKeyType.description: Represents the cipher key type of hpnicfDot11CipherKey.

hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.name: hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtTable
hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the radio policy of each radio. It can't be modified if the radio policy is a default radio policy.

hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.name: hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry
hpnicfDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

hpnicfDot11RPAPSerialID.name: hpnicfDot11RPAPSerialID
hpnicfDot11RPAPSerialID.description: This object represents the Serial ID of AP.

hpnicfDot11RPBeaconInterval.name: hpnicfDot11RPBeaconInterval
hpnicfDot11RPBeaconInterval.description: This object represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hpnicfDot11RPDtimInterval.name: hpnicfDot11RPDtimInterval
hpnicfDot11RPDtimInterval.description: This object represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmissions of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

hpnicfDot11RPRtsThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11RPRtsThreshold
hpnicfDot11RPRtsThreshold.description: This object represents the current minimum size, in octets, of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

hpnicfDot11RPFragThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11RPFragThreshold
hpnicfDot11RPFragThreshold.description: This object represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

hpnicfDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11RPShortRetryThreshold
hpnicfDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to hpnicfDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hpnicfDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.name: hpnicfDot11RPLongRetryThreshold
hpnicfDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than hpnicfDot11RTSThreshold, and that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hpnicfDot11RPClientMaxCount.name: hpnicfDot11RPClientMaxCount
hpnicfDot11RPClientMaxCount.description: This object represents the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityTable
hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.description: This table defines the WLAN security status for ESS, BSS and WLAN-Ethernet interface which binding the crypto service-template. Otherwise, when binding the clear service-template, hpnicfPortSecurityTables should be used to configure port security.

hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry
hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.description: There is a row in this table for service policy.

hpnicfDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityServicePolicyID
hpnicfDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityMode
hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions The default value, no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.name: hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityKeyType
hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone - This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key - This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key - This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.name: hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode
hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.name: hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString
hpnicfDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.description: This is the password string used for psk authentication.

hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM
hpnicfDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. none - The default value, no any security mode is set. psk - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). radius - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). wlanex - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated by wlan cert.

hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable
hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.description: The table defines the parameters of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.name: hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry
hpnicfDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

hpnicfDot11SPEnable.name: hpnicfDot11SPEnable
hpnicfDot11SPEnable.description: Represents whether the service policy is enabled.

hpnicfDot11APTemplateTable.name: hpnicfDot11APTemplateTable
hpnicfDot11APTemplateTable.description: By AP template CLI, administrator will configure the parameters of AP by convenience. Before AP boot up and connect to AC by CAPWAP tunnel, administrator will create AP template for each AP. When AP connect to AC, AC will assign configuration to AP by hpnicfDot11APSerialID information in AP template.

hpnicfDot11APTemplateEntry.name: hpnicfDot11APTemplateEntry
hpnicfDot11APTemplateEntry.description: Each entry contains configuration information for each AP.

hpnicfDot11APTemplateName.name: hpnicfDot11APTemplateName
hpnicfDot11APTemplateName.description: Represents the name of AP template.

hpnicfDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.name: hpnicfDot11TemplateAPModelAlias
hpnicfDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.description: Represents the alias of AP model name.

hpnicfDot11Description.name: hpnicfDot11Description
hpnicfDot11Description.description: This attribute will give more information about AP. Administrator could suggest the location, owner or other information for each AP. If the value is set to NULL, the description will be removed.

hpnicfDot11APWorkMode.name: hpnicfDot11APWorkMode
hpnicfDot11APWorkMode.description: Represents what work mode for AP. The following values are supported: normal - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

hpnicfDot11APTemplateRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11APTemplateRowStatus
hpnicfDot11APTemplateRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11StatisInterv.name: hpnicfDot11StatisInterv
hpnicfDot11StatisInterv.description: Represents the interval of radio statistic.

hpnicfDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.name: hpnicfDot11APBroadcastProbeReply
hpnicfDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.name: hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerInterv
hpnicfDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

hpnicfDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.name: hpnicfDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv
hpnicfDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA.

hpnicfDot11APCir.name: hpnicfDot11APCir
hpnicfDot11APCir.description: Represents the committed information rate between AP and AC.

hpnicfDot11APCbs.name: hpnicfDot11APCbs

hpnicfDot11APElementID.name: hpnicfDot11APElementID

hpnicfDot11PortSecurityEntry.description: There is a row in this table for each ESS, BSS and WLAN-Ethernet interface.It is indexed using the object ifIndex in RFC1213-MIB.

hpnicfDot11PortSecurityMode.name: hpnicfDot11PortSecurityMode
hpnicfDot11PortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions - The default value,no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk - The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk - This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

hpnicfDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType
hpnicfDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone - This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key - This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key - This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyMode
hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, hpnicfDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, hpnicfDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyString.name: hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyString
hpnicfDot11SecurityPskKeyString.description: This is the password string used for psk authentication.
